g(logCtx, \\\"sessionHasNewContent: no staged files, returning transcript growth\\\",\\n1305:// sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript checks if a session has new content\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"uuid\":\"32304a19-cce9-499c-92ab-399a0f590b92\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T05:34:28.690Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a6229bd1f50cd3aaa\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Lh1dedjCiKw4fn5qEigphf\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_013vHvpZEFHR2pkkgoi7zzY9\",\"uuid\":\"d52a3181-a061-4a8d-aaac-584babdffe3e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T05:34:28.692Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d52a3181-a061-4a8d-aaac-584babdffe3e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_013vHvpZEFHR2pkkgoi7zzY9\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_013vHvpZEFHR2pkkgoi7zzY9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T05:35:25.422Z\",\"uuid\":\"439eacdf-86d7-48e6-8b96-87f5fce5e8ea\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e9ffce19-3958-4a25-813b-f0ae2ccd89b6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_013vHvpZEFHR2pkkgoi7zzY9\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now I have enough context. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document:\\n\\n## Detailed Hook Analysis Report\\n\\n### Overview\\nThe CLI uses two critical git hooks in the manual-commit strategy:\\n1. **prepare-commit-msg** - Runs BEFORE user commits, adds checkpoint trailer\\n2. **post-commit** - Runs AFTER commit completes, condenses session data\\n\\n---\\n\\n## HOOK 1: prepare-commit-msg\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (lines 285-476)\\n\\n**Purpose:** Add `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer to commit messages when agent session content exists\\n\\n### Step-by-Step Flow\\n\\n```\\n1. Early Validation (non-blocking)\\n   ├─ Check if running during rebase/cherry-pick/revert\\n   │  └─ Stat fs calls: .git/rebase-merge/, .git/rebase-apply/, .git/CHERRY_PICK_HEAD, .git/REVERT_HEAD\\n   │\\n   ├─ Skip for merge/squash sources (auto-generated messages)\\n   │\\n   ├─ Handle amend specially (source=\\\"commit\\\")\\n   │  └─ Jump to handleAmendCommitMsg (line 478-556)\\n   │\\n   ├─ Open git repository\\n   │  └─ go-git repo open (PERF HIT #1)\\n   │\\n   └─ Get worktree root (fs realpath call)\\n\\n2. Find Active Sessions\\n   ├─ Query all session states from disk\\n   │  └─ StateStore.List() reads .git/entire-sessions/*.json files (PERF HIT #2)\\n   │     - Filters out orphaned sessions by checking if shadow branch exists\\n   │     - For each session: repo.Reference(plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(shadowBranch), true)\\n   │     - MANY git ref lookups if multiple sessions exist!\\n   │\\n   └─ Return if no sessions found\\n\\n3. Fast Path for Agent Commits (no TTY)\\n   ├─ If hasTTY() returns false (running under agent, CI, etc)\\n   │  └─ Find first ACTIVE session\\n   │     └─ Call addTrailerForAgentCommit() and RETURN early\\n   │        └─ This path SKIPS expensive content detection\\n   │\\n   └─ Continue to slow path if TTY available\\n\\n4. Content Detection (EXPENSIVE)\\n   ├─ Call filterSessionsWithNewContent(ctx, repo, sessions)\\n   │  │\\n   │  └─ For each session, call sessionHasNewContent() which does:\\n   │     ├─ If shadow branch exists:\\n   │     │  ├─ repo.Reference() to get shadow ref (git ref lookup)\\n   │     │  ├─ repo.CommitObject() to get shadow commit (git object read)\\n   │     │  ├─ commit.Tree() to get shadow tree (git tree object read)\\n   │     │  ├─ Either:\\n   │     │  │  ├─ Check if staged files overlap with shadow tree\\n   │     │  │  │  └─ Calls filesOverlapWithContent():\\n   │     │  │  │     ├─ Walk shadow tree for each stage file (tree traversal)\\n   │     │  │  │     └─ Parse transcript for changes (file I/O + JSON parsing)\\n   │     │  │  │\\n   │     │  │  └─ Or check if transcript grew since CheckpointTranscriptStart\\n   │     │  │     └─ Read live transcript from disk (file I/O)\\n   │     │  │\\n   │     │  └─ Return true/false based on content checks\\n   │     │\\n   │     └─ No shadow branch: check live transcript from disk\\n   │        └─ Read .entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl file\\n   │\\n   ├─ Return only sessions with new content\\n   │\\n   └─ If no sessions with content found: RETURN early (no trailer needed)\\n\\n5. Generate Checkpoint ID\\n   ├─ id.Generate() - random 12-hex-char ID (cryptographic operation)\\n   │\\n   └─ Store in checkpointID variable\\n\\n6. TTY-Based Confirmation (If source=\\\"message\\\")\\n   ├─ If using -m or -F flag (explicit message):\\n   │  ├─ Check commit_linking setting\\n   │  │  └─ Load settings.json (file I/O)\\n   │  │\\n   │  └─ If TTY available and not \\\"always\\\" setting:\\n   │     ├─ Open /dev/tty (file I/O)\\n   │     ├─ Display prompt with last prompt text\\n   │     ├─ Read user response from /dev/tty (blocking I/O!)\\n   │     └─ If \\\"always\\\" chosen:\\n   │        └─ saveCommitLinkingAlways() - write to settings.local.json (file I/O)\\n   │\\n   └─ Add trailer to commit message\\n\\n7. Write Message Back\\n   └─ WriteFile(commitMsgFile, ...) (file I/O)\\n```\\n\\n### Git/IO Operations in prepare-commit-msg\\n\\n| Operation | Type | Frequency | Notes |\\n|-----------|------|-----------|-------|\\n| **Repository open** | go-git | Once | ~20-50ms cold, cached after |\\n| **StateStore.List()** | Filesystem | Once | Reads all session files from .git/entire-sessions/ |\\n| **repo.Reference()** (shadow branch check) | go-git | N sessions | For orphan cleanup in list operation |\\n| **repo.Reference()** (content check) | go-git | N sessions | Per session to verify shadow exists |\\n| **repo.CommitObject()** | go-git | N sessions | Get shadow commit for tree |\\n| **commit.Tree()** | go-git | N sessions | Get shadow tree for overlap check |\\n| **filesOverlapWithContent()** | Algorithm | N sessions | Tree walk + transcript parse (EXPENSIVE) |\\n| **Transcript reads** | Filesystem | Per session | Read live .entire/metadata/<id>/full.jsonl |\\n| **Settings load** | Filesystem | Once (conditional) | Only if source=\\\"message\\\" |\\n| **TTY I/O** | Blocking I/O | Conditional | Only if TTY + source=\\\"message\\\" + not \\\"always\\\" |\\n\\n### Performance Bottlenecks in prepare-commit-msg\\n\\n1. **CRITICAL: filesOverlapWithContent calls** (lines 1244-1297)\\n   - Called for EVERY session when checking if content exists\\n   - For each session: walks shadow tree, parses transcript\\n   - Quadratic complexity with multiple sessions or large transcripts\\n   - Tree walk is O(n) where n = tree entries\\n   - Transcript parse is O(m) where m = transcript lines\\n\\n2. **Multiple repo.Reference() calls**\\n   - StateStore.List() calls ref lookup for each session's shadow branch (orphan cleanup)\\n   - Then sessionHasNewContent calls ref lookup AGAIN per session\\n   - Total: 2+ ref lookups per session\\n\\n3. **Tree operations**\\n   - repo.CommitObject() + commit.Tree() per session\\n   - These are sequential reads from git object database\\n   - Not cached between sessions\\n\\n4. **TTY blocking I/O**\\n   - If user runs `git commit -m` with active session\\n   - Hook blocks on /dev/tty read (user must respond)\\n   - Can hang if no TTY available despite check\\n\\n---\\n\\n## HOOK 2: post-commit\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (lines 720-993)\\n\\n**Purpose:** Condense session checkpoints to permanent storage when commit is made\\n\\n### Step-by-Step Flow\\n\\n```\\n1. Early Validation\\n   ├─ Open git repository\\n   │  └─ go-git repo open (PERF HIT #1)\\n   │\\n   ├─ Get HEAD commit\\n   │  └─ repo.Head() + repo.CommitObject() (git ops)\\n   │\\n   ├─ Check if commit has Entire-Checkpoint trailer\\n   │  ├─ trailers.ParseCheckpoint(commit.Message)\\n   │  │\\n   │  ├─ If NO trailer:\\n   │  │  └─ postCommitUpdateBaseCommitOnly():\\n   │  │     ├─ List all sessions (StateStore.List())\\n   │  │     └─ Update BaseCommit to HEAD for ACTIVE sessions only\\n   │  │        └─ EARLY RETURN (no condensation)\\n   │  │\\n   │  └─ Continue if trailer found\\n   │\\n   └─ Get worktree root\\n\\n2. Find Sessions & Build Context\\n   ├─ List all sessions for worktree\\n   │  └─ s.findSessionsForWorktree() → s.listAllSessionStates()\\n   │     └─ StateStore.List() (filesystem reads)\\n   │\\n   ├─ Check for rebase/sequence in progress\\n   │  └─ isGitSequenceOperation() (filesystem stats)\\n   │\\n   └─ Build TransitionContext for state machine\\n\\n3. Pre-Resolve HEAD Tree (ONE TIME for all sessions!)\\n   ├─ commit.Tree()\\n   │  └─ Get tree for HEAD commit (git object read - CACHED)\\n   │\\n   ├─ commit.Parent(0).Tree()\\n   │  └─ Get tree for HEAD's parent (git object read - CACHED)\\n   │\\n   └─ filesChangedInCommit(commit, headTree, parentTree)\\n      └─ Tree diff: compare HEAD vs parent trees\\n         - Walk both trees O(n) where n = tree entries\\n         - Build map of files changed in this commit\\n\\n4. Loop: Process Each Session\\n   │\\n   ├─ For each session in sessions:\\n   │  │\\n   │  ├─ Skip if FullyCondensed && PhaseEnded (optimization)\\n   │  │\\n   │  ├─ Call postCommitProcessSession() which does:\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ PRE-RESOLVE per-session git objects:\\n   │  │  │  ├─ repo.Reference(shadowBranch) (git ref lookup)\\n   │  │  │  ├─ repo.CommitObject(shadowRef.Hash()) (git object read)\\n   │  │  │  └─ shadowCommit.Tree() (git tree read)\\n   │  │  │     └─ CACHED in handler for later use\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Check if session has new content:\\n   │  │  │  └─ If ACTIVE: assume true (optimize, trust PrepareCommitMsg)\\n   │  │  │  └─ If IDLE/ENDED: call sessionHasNewContent()\\n   │  │  │     └─ SAME expensive checks as PrepareCommitMsg:\\n   │  │  │        - filesOverlapWithContent() tree walk + transcript parse\\n   │  │  │        - Or check live transcript growth\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Extract FilesTouched from state (or from live transcript if ACTIVE mid-commit)\\n   │  │  │  └─ s.extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(state) (file I/O)\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ State Machine Transition:\\n   │  │  │  └─ TransitionAndLog(state, EventGitCommit, handler)\\n   │  │  │     └─ Calls phase machine, which calls handler methods\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Handler: HandleCondense or HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched\\n   │  │  │  │\\n   │  │  │  ├─ shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck():\\n   │  │  │  │  ├─ If ACTIVE + recent interaction: skip overlap check (fast)\\n   │  │  │  │  │\\n   │  │  │  │  └─ Otherwise: filesOverlapWithContent() (tree walk)\\n   │  │  │  │     └─ THIRD TIME content overlap is checked for this session!\\n   │  │  │  │\\n   │  │  │  └─ If should condense:\\n   │  │  │     └─ condenseAndUpdateState():\\n   │  │  │        └─ s.CondenseSession() (THE EXPENSIVE OPERATION)\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Record checkpoint ID if condensed and ACTIVE\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Carry-forward logic:\\n   │  │  │  └─ filesWithRemainingAgentChanges():\\n   │  │  │     └─ Compare shadow tree vs committed files (another tree walk!)\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  ├─ Update FilesTouched for next commit\\n   │  │  │\\n   │  │  └─ Save session state to disk\\n   │  │     └─ StateStore.Save() (file I/O + atomic write)\\n   │  │\\n   │  └─ Track shadow branch for cleanup\\n   │\\n   └─ For each shadow branch marked for deletion:\\n      ├─ Check if any ACTIVE uncondensed sessions still need it\\n      │\\n      └─ If safe to delete:\\n         └─ DeleteBranchCLI(branchName) (git CLI call)\\n```\\n\\n### Git/IO Operations in post-commit\\n\\n| Operation | Type | Frequency | Notes |\\n|-----------|------|-----------|-------|\\n| **Repository open** | go-git | Once | ~20-50ms |\\n| **repo.Head()** | go-git | Once | Get HEAD ref |\\n| **repo.CommitObject(HEAD)** | go-git | Once | Get HEAD commit object |\\n| **commit.Tree()** | go-git | Once (HEAD) | Cached, reused |\\n| **commit.Parent(0).Tree()** | go-git | Once (parent) | Cached, reused |\\n| **filesChangedInCommit()** | Algorithm | Once | Tree diff O(n) |\\n| **StateStore.List()** | Filesystem | 1-2x | Session file reads |\\n| **repo.Reference(shadowBranch)** | go-git | N sessions | Per-session shadow ref lookup |\\n| **repo.CommitObject(shadowHash)** | go-git | N sessions | Per-session shadow commit |\\n| **shadowCommit.Tree()** | go-git | N sessions | Per-session shadow tree (cached) |\\n| **sessionHasNewContent()** | Algorithm | N IDLE/ENDED | Content overlap checks |\\n| **filesOverlapWithContent()** | Algorithm | 1-3x per session | Tree walk + transcript parse |\\n| **extractFilesFromLiveTranscript()** | Filesystem | ACTIVE mid-commit | Read live transcript |\\n| **CondenseSession()** | Complex | N sessions | (see below) |\\n| **filesWithRemainingAgentChanges()** | Algorithm | N sessions | Tree comparison for carry-forward |\\n| **StateStore.Save()** | Filesystem | N sessions | Save updated state file |\\n| **DeleteBranchCLI()** | git CLI | ~M branches | Delete shadow branches |\\n\\n### CondenseSession Deep Dive (lines 122-292 of manual_commit_condensation.go)\\n\\nThis is the MOST EXPENSIVE operation in post-commit:\\n\\n```\\nCondenseSession(checkpointID, state, committedFiles) {\\n   \\n   1. Get/Resolve Shadow Branch\\n      ├─ repo.Reference(shadowBranch) (ALREADY done by caller!)\\n      │  └─ DUPLICATE LOOKUP if not pre-resolved\\n      │\\n      ├─ repo.CommitObject(ref.Hash()) (DUPLICATE if not cached)\\n      │\\n      └─ Commit.Tree() (DUPLICATE if not cached)\\n\\n   2. Extract Session Data (EXPENSIVE)\\n      ├─ If shadow branch exists:\\n      │  └─ extractSessionData():\\n      │     ├─ repo.TreeIter for shadow tree\\n      │     │  └─ Tree walk to read all files O(n)\\n      │     │\\n      │     ├─ Filter to FilesTouched (reduce to relevant files)\\n      │     │\\n      │     └─ Read transcript from shadow commit or live file\\n      │        └─ File I/O + JSON/JSONL parsing\\n      │\\n      └─ Else (no shadow branch, mid-session commit):\\n         ├─ prepareTranscriptIfNeeded():\\n         │  └─ If OpenCode: run `opencode export` (SUBPROCESS!)\\n         │     └─ Blocks waiting for OpenCode to export\\n         │\\n         └─ extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript():\\n            └─ Read live transcript file and parse\\n\\n   3. Filter Files to Committed Set\\n      ├─ If committedFiles provided:\\n      │  └─ Intersect FilesTouched ∩ committedFiles\\n      │     └─ O(m) where m = files touched\\n      │\\n      └─ Use committed files as fallback if no tracked files\\n\\n   4. Calculate Attribution\\n      └─ calculateSessionAttributions(repo, ref, sessionData, state):\\n         ├─ Get AttributionBaseCommit tree\\n         │  └─ repo.CommitObject(attributionBaseCommit)\\n         │     └─ repo.CommitObject + tree (ANOTHER git read!)\\n         │\\n         ├─ For each file in FilesTouched:\\n         │  └─ Diff: base tree vs shadow tree (per-file diffs)\\n         │     └─ Line-level attribution calculation O(k) where k = file lines\\n         │\\n         └─ Count user vs agent changes per file\\n\\n   5. Generate Summary (OPTIONAL, if enabled)\\n      └─ summarize.GenerateFromTranscript():\\n         ├─ Make API call to summarization service\\n         │  └─ BLOCKING NETWORK I/O (can be slow)\\n         │\\n         └─ Return summary or error (non-fatal)\\n\\n   6. Write to Checkpoint Store\\n      └─ store.WriteCommitted():\\n         ├─ Build checkpoint metadata JSON\\n         │\\n         ├─ Create tree structure on entire/checkpoints/v1:\\n         │  └─ <checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/\\n         │     ├─ metadata.json (checkpoint summary)\\n         │     ├─ 0/ (first session's data)\\n         │     │  ├─ metadata.json\\n         │     │  ├─ full.jsonl (transcript)\\n         │     │  ├─ prompt.txt\\n         │     │  └─ context.md\\n         │     │\\n         │     └─ ... (more sessions if multi-session)\\n         │\\n         └─ Create commit on entire/checkpoints/v1\\n            ├─ repo.CommitObject() to get metadata tree objects\\n            │  └─ Tree building via go-git plumbing APIs\\n            │\\n            └─ Create orphan commit\\n               └─ Git object creation (relatively fast)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Performance Bottlenecks in post-commit\\n\\n1. **CRITICAL: filesOverlapWithContent called 3+ times per session**\\n   - Once in sessionHasNewContent (if IDLE/ENDED)\\n   - Once in shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck\\n   - Once in filesWithRemainingAgentChanges\\n   - Each call: tree walk + transcript parse\\n   - **Optimization opportunity**: Cache result after first call\\n\\n2. **CRITICAL: CondenseSession called per session**\\n   - Expensive operations:\\n     - extractSessionData: tree walk O(n)\\n     - calculateSessionAttributions: line-level diffs O(k) per file\\n     - summarize.GenerateFromTranscript: API call (blocking!)\\n     - WriteCommitted: tree building + commit creation\\n   - **Total time**: 100-500ms per session depending on transcript size\\n\\n3. **Duplicate git object reads**\\n   - postCommitProcessSession pre-resolves shadow ref/tree\\n   - But CondenseSession re-reads if opts not passed correctly\\n   - Pre-resolved objects ARE passed via condenseOpts parameter (good)\\n\\n4. **Filesystem bottleneck: StateStore.List() called twice**\\n   - Once in findSessionsForWorktree (line 754)\\n   - Reads all session files from .git/entire-sessions/\\n   - Each file: JSON parse\\n   - **Optimization**: Cache result or refactor to single list\\n\\n5. **Carry-forward tree comparison**\\n   - filesWithRemainingAgentChanges(): compares shadow tree vs committed files\\n   - Tree walk is O(n) even if only checking a few files\\n   - Called for every condensed session\\n\\n6. **Optional: Summarization API call**\\n   - If summarization enabled: blocking network I/O\\n   - Can add 1-10+ seconds per session\\n   - Non-fatal but impact visible to user\\n\\n### State Machine Phase Transitions\\n\\nThe post-commit handler implements session.ActionHandler to execute phase-based actions:\\n\\n```go\\n// For EventGitCommit:\\n// ACTIVE + GitCommit → ACTIVE (state stays active, next turn might commit again)\\n// IDLE + GitCommit → IDLE (state stays idle)\\n// ENDED + GitCommit → ENDED (state stays ended)\\n\\n// Handler methods called:\\n// ActionCondense → HandleCondense() → condenseAndUpdateState()\\n// ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched → HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched() → condenseAndUpdateState()\\n// ActionDiscardIfNoFiles → HandleDiscardIfNoFiles() → updateBaseCommitIfChanged()\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary: Operation Counts per Hook Invocation\\n\\n### prepare-commit-msg (single commit)\\n- **Fast path (no TTY, ACTIVE session):**\\n  - 1x repo open\\n  - 1x StateStore.List() + ref lookups for orphan cleanup\\n  - 1x trailer generation\\n  - Total: ~30-100ms\\n\\n- **Slow path (content detection, multiple sessions):**\\n  - 1x repo open\\n  - N x repo.Reference() for shadow branch checks\\n  - N x sessionHasNewContent() calls which include:\\n    - repo.CommitObject() + tree reads\\n    - filesOverlapWithContent() tree walks\\n    - Transcript file I/O\\n  - 1x Settings load (if source=\\\"message\\\")\\n  - 1x TTY I/O (if prompted)\\n  - Total: **500ms - 5s** depending on N sessions and transcript size\\n\\n### post-commit (single commit with trailer)\\n- 1x repo open\\n- 1x HEAD + parent tree pre-resolution (cached)\\n- 1x filesChangedInCommit() tree diff\\n- 1x StateStore.List()\\n- For each session:\\n  - 1x repo.Reference() shadow branch\\n  - 1x repo.CommitObject() + tree (cached)\\n  - 1x sessionHasNewContent() if not ACTIVE\\n  - 1x shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()\\n  - 1x CondenseSession() if condensing:\\n    - extractSessionData() tree walk + transcript parse\\n    - calculateSessionAttributions() diff calculations\\n    - optional: summarize API call (1-10s+)\\n    - WriteCommitted() tree building + commit\\n  - 1x filesWithRemainingAgentChanges() tree comparison\\n  - 1x StateStore.Save()\\n  - ~1-5x filesOverlapWithContent() calls\\n- Cleanup shadow branches\\n\\n- Total: **500ms - 10s+** per session depending on:\\n  - Number of sessions\\n  - Transcript size\\n  - Summarization enabled\\n  - File change volume\\n\\n### Combined worst case (human commits with active session)\\n1. prepare-commit-msg runs → 500ms - 5s (content detection)\\n2. User edits message → interactive\\n3. post-commit runs → 500ms - 10s+ (condensation)\\n\\n**Total user-visible time: 1-15s+** depending on circumstances\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Lock Acquisition Analysis\\n\\n**Git locks acquired:**\\n- None explicitly (go-git handles internally)\\n- But `.git/index.lock` held during hook execution by git itself\\n- Shadow branches can conflict if concurrent sessions → race conditions possible\\n\\n**Filesystem locks:**\\n- StateStore.Save() does atomic write (create temp, rename)\\n- Settings.local.json write (if \\\"always\\\" chosen)\\n- No explicit locking, relies on filesystem atomicity\\n\\n**Potential deadlocks:**\\n- If summarize API hangs: post-commit blocks indefinitely\\n- If transcript file locked: extraction fails but falls back\\n- If TTY unavailable but TTY check passes (race): can hang\\n\\n---\\n\\nThis analysis shows the hooks have significant performance variability based on session