xternal\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01NP4XR76MQt8o98y9zcSWKc\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package strategy\\n     2→\\n     3→import (\\n     4→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n     5→\\t\\\"io\\\"\\n     6→\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n     9→\\n    10→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n    11→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5\\\"\\n    12→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object\\\"\\n    14→)\\n    15→\\n    16→// Content-aware overlap detection for checkpoint management.\\n    17→//\\n    18→// These functions determine whether a commit contains session-related work by comparing\\n    19→// file content (not just filenames) against the shadow branch. This enables accurate\\n    20→// detection of the \\\"reverted and replaced\\\" scenario where a user:\\n    21→// 1. Reverts session changes (e.g., git checkout -- file.txt)\\n    22→// 2. Creates completely different content in the same file\\n    23→// 3. Commits the new content\\n    24→//\\n    25→// In this scenario, the commit should NOT get a checkpoint trailer because the\\n    26→// session's work was discarded, not incorporated.\\n    27→//\\n    28→// The key distinction:\\n    29→// - Modified files (exist in parent commit): Always count as overlap, regardless of\\n    30→//   content changes. The user is editing session's work.\\n    31→// - New files (don't exist in parent): Require content match against shadow branch.\\n    32→//   If content differs completely, the session's work was likely reverted & replaced.\\n    33→\\n    34→// overlapOpts provides pre-resolved git objects