gs lost, next agent session orphaned\\n- **Mitigation:** Child logs to `.entire/logs/` files; daemon can catch and retry on next enable\\n- **Acceptable:** Logs are checkpoint-grade best-effort\\n\\n### Risk 2: Parent Dies Before Release()\\n- **Impact:** Process becomes zombie briefly\\n- **Mitigation:** Go runtime handles zombie reaping; `Process.Release()` ensures clean separation\\n- **Reality:** Tested in production telemetry for 2+ years\\n\\n### Risk 3: Concurrent Background Processes\\n- **Scenario:** Two commits in rapid succession\\n- **Impact:** Multiple background processes condensing same shadow branch\\n- **Mitigation:** Lock files in shadow branch metadata; first writer wins\\n- **Current behavior:** Handled in existing `CondenseSession` logic\\n\\n### Risk 4: Git Hook Timeout\\n- **Scenario:** System suspends after git commit, before background process finishes\\n- **Impact:** Session logs not condensed to `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- **Mitigation:** Rewind still works from shadow branch; next commit triggers cleanup\\n- **Acceptable:** Better than blocking git for 30+ seconds\\n\\n### Risk 5: Signal Handling in Background Process\\n- **SIGTERM to hook parent:** Background child unaffected (Setpgid isolation)\\n- **SIGTERM to background child:** Process terminates; logs to .git/entire-sessions/ not updated\\n- **Mitigation:** Child catches signals and gracefully saves state before exiting\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File Structure Implications\\n\\nNo new files needed in `.entire/`:\\n- Condensation metadata goes to `entire/checkpoints/v1` (existing)\\n- Session state goes to `.git/entire-sessions/` (existing)\\n- Logs go to `.entire/logs/` (existing)\\n\\nBackground child process uses **same paths** as parent - file-based locking handles concurrent access.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary Decision Table\\n\\n| Approach | When to Use | Codebase Fit | Recommendation |\\n|----------|------------|-------------|-----------------|\\n| 1: exec.Command (no Setpgid) | Simple cases, same-machine | ✅ Excellent | ✅ Acceptable for post-commit |\\n| 2: + Setpgid (Recommended) | Production robustness | ✅ Perfect | ✅✅ **Use This** |\\n| 3: Double-fork | Unix purism, overkill | ⚠️ Unnecessary | ❌ Skip (Approach 2 is simpler) |\\n| 4: Job queue + daemon | Cross-platform, reliability | ✅ Good for scaling | ⚠️ Overkill now; consider for future multi-hook design |\\n\\n**Final Recommendation:** **Implement Approach 2 (Goroutine + Setpgid)** - matches existing telemetry pattern, simple, reliable, and fits the Unix hook model perfectly.\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":94259,\"totalTokens\":80418,\"totalToolUseCount\":33,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":195,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":75197,\"output_tokens\":5026,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":195,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"517978d6-add2-430e-a8bc-2fff337b3fad\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b83f2bf6-3f46-4571-a154-a59db67cf7d3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015wZFrgbRQGbJ2m2vsGCGzY\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good research. The codebase already has an exact precedent for this. Let me look at the telemetry implementation to confirm the pattern.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":5595,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":104851,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":5595},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard