\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01V13KWZVVJ29iSYQbAx58Ws\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good — the shell hook is `entire hooks git post-commit 2>/dev/null || true`. Now I have the full picture. Here's the summary:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## How to Background Post-Commit\\n\\n### The Pattern (proven in codebase)\\n\\nThe telemetry module (`telemetry/detached_unix.go`) already does exactly this:\\n\\n```go\\ncmd := exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), executable, \\\"__send_analytics\\\", payload)\\ncmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{Setpgid: true}\\ncmd.Dir = \\\"/\\\"\\ncmd.Stdout = io.Discard\\ncmd.Stderr = io.Discard\\ncmd.Start()\\ncmd.Process.Release()\\n```\\n\\nThe child process is detached from the parent's process group, survives parent exit, and runs independently. Works on macOS and Linux.\\n\\n### The Design for Post-Commit\\n\\n**Split PostCommit into two phases:**\\n\\n| Phase | Runs As | Time | Work |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| **Sync** | Hook process | ~30-50ms | Read HEAD, check trailer, find sessions, update BaseCommit, spawn background |\\n| **Background** | Detached child | 200ms-15s | CondenseSession, attribution, summarization, WriteCommitted, shadow branch cleanup |\\n\\n**Invocation chain:**\\n```\\ngit commit\\n  → shell hook: `entire hooks git post-commit 2>/dev/null || true`\\n    → PostCommit (sync): check trailer, spawn child, return 0\\n      → detached: `entire hooks git post-commit --background --checkpoint-id X --repo-root /path`\\n        → PostCommitBackground: condensation, attribution, summarization, write, cleanup\\n```\\n\\n### Context Passing\\n\\nThe background process needs:\\n- **Checkpoint ID** — from the trailer in HEAD commit\\n- **Repo root** — so it can re-open the repo without relying on cwd\\n- **Session IDs** — which sessions to condense (or re-discover from session state files)\\n\\nTwo options:\\n1. **CLI args** (like telemetry): `--checkpoint-id a3b2c4d5e6f7 --repo-root /path/to/repo`\\n2. **Re-derive in child**: child opens repo at repo-root, reads HEAD, re-discovers sessions — same logic as current PostCommit but in a fresh process\\n\\nOption 2 is simpler because it avoids serializing intermediate state. The child process just runs the same `PostCommit` logic, but invoked differently.\\n\\n### Key Tradeoffs\\n\\n**1. State consistency between rapid commits**\\nThis is the main risk. If user commits twice in quick succession:\\n- Commit 1's background condensation is running\\n- Commit 2's prepare-commit-msg needs to check session state\\n\\nMitigation: The sync phase updates `BaseCommit` and session phase *before* spawning background. The background only writes to `entire/checkpoints/v1` (separate branch) and deletes shadow branches. A lock file in `.git/entire-sessions/condense.lock` prevents concurrent background processes from conflicting.\\n\\n**2. Shadow branch deleted before next SaveStep**\\nIf background cleanup deletes the shadow branch while an agent is still running, the next `SaveStep` would need to recreate it. This already happens today (shadow branch is created on first SaveStep if missing).\\n\\n**3. `entire explain` immediately after commit**\\nIf user runs `entire explain` before background finishes, the checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1` may not exist yet. Need a \\\"pending\\\" state or fall back to shadow branch data.\\n\\n**4. Background process crashes silently**\\nThe `2>/dev/null || true` in the hook script means crashes are invisible. Mitigation: log to `.entire/logs/` (the background process re-inits logging).\\n\\n### What Changes\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|---|---|\\n| `hooks_git_cmd.go` | Add `--background` flag to `post-commit` command |\\n| `manual_commit_hooks.go` | Split `PostCommit()` into sync + `PostCommitBackground()` |\\n| New: `strategy/background_unix.go` | `spawnBackgroundPostCommit()` — same pattern as `detached_unix.go` |\\n| New: `strategy/background_other.go` | No-op on non-Unix (fallback to synchronous) |\\n\\nThe shell hook script (`hooks.go`) stays **unchanged** — the backgrounding is handled inside the Go binary.\\n\\n### Quick Win Alternative\\n\\nIf a full split feels risky, **backgrounding just the summarization** is much simpler:\\n- Move `summarize.GenerateFromTranscript()` to a goroutine, fire-and-forget\\n- Write summary to `entire/checkpoints/v1` asynchronously\\n- Everything else stays synchronous\\n- Saves 2-15s with zero state consistency risk\\n\\nWant me to start implementing either approach?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":611,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":116490,\"output_tokens\":1163,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":611,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYfcmkCKAvs26z3e2pFNr\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"434f38b5-f5c9-4a8c-acb0-c847f9c89ef9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T05:46:23.870Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"434f38b5-f5c9-4a8c-acb0-c847f9c89ef9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"dd6e111c-5e70-4679-a528-585d3f5e7202\",\"toolUseID\":\"dd6e111c-5e70-4679-a528-585d3f5e7202\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03