a3608\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_018fkoRaSZhyJ1a1V3x99zwR\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01VarZyj11kPWsSzK55MpJQ1\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3/tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md\",\"content\":\"# Commit Hook Performance Investigation\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nUsers report commit hooks are slow. Measured **6.3 seconds** for a simple commit in a large repo (rust-lang, ~58k files).\\n\\n## Timing Instrumentation\\n\\nAdded timing logs to `PrepareCommitMsg`, `PostCommit`, and `CondenseSession`. Tested on rust-lang repo (~58k files), single session (idle), 1 file committed.\\n\\nBranch with instrumentation: `alex/investigate-commit-slowness`\\n\\nFiles modified:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — timing in PrepareCommitMsg + PostCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — timing in CondenseSession\\n\\nTo read results: `grep 'timing' .entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n## Measured Breakdown\\n\\n### prepare-commit-msg: ~121ms total\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 104ms | go-git PlainOpenWithOptions |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.3ms | |\\n| filterSessionsWithNewContent | 114ms | Content overlap detection |\\n\\n### post-commit: ~5,436ms total (5.4s) — THE BOTTLENECK\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 0.08ms | Likely cached from prepare-commit-msg |\\n| Head+CommitObject | 0.1ms | |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.1ms | |\\n| **resolveTreesAndDiff** | **703ms** | `filesChangedInCommit` walks both HEAD and parent trees |\\n| **processSession[0] (idle)** | **4,712ms** | Condensation of one session |\\n| processSession[1] (ended) | 0.8ms | |\\n| shadowBranchCleanup | 16ms | |\\n\\n### Inside processSession — CondenseSession: ~4,706ms\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms | |\\n| **calculateAttribution** | **4,685ms** | **86% of total commit time** |\\n| WriteCommitted | 18ms | |\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n### Primary: `calculateAttribution` — 4.7s (86% of total)\\n\\n`CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated()` in `manual_commit_attribution.go` calls `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees(ctx, baseTree, headTree)` at line ~229.\\n\\nThis function:\\n1. Calls `baseTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in base tree\\n2. Calls `headTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in HEAD tree\\n3. Builds two hash maps of every file path → blob hash\\n4. Compares to find changed files\\n\\nThis is **O(total files in repo)** when it should be **O(files changed in commit)**.\\n\\nThe `committedFileSet` (files changed in this commit) is already computed by `filesChangedInCommit` earlier in PostCommit. Attribution only needs to diff non-agent files from this set, not discover them by walking entire trees.\\n\\n### Secondary: `resolveTreesAndDiff` — 703ms\\n\\n`filesChangedInCommit()` in `common.go` also walks both HEAD and parent trees to find changed files. Same O(n) full-tree-walk problem.\\n\\nCould be replaced with `git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r HEAD~1 HEAD` which uses git's internal index and is much faster than go-git tree iteration.\\n\\n### Everything else is fast\\n\\n| Operation | Time |\\n|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository (first call) | 104ms |\\n| OpenRepository (second call) | <1ms |\\n| Session state listing | <1ms |\\n| Content overlap detection | 114ms |\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms |\\n| WriteCommitted (tree build + commit on checkpoints branch) | 18ms |\\n| Shadow branch cleanup | 16ms |\\n\\n## Proposed Fix: Pass committedFileSet to Attribution\\n\\nInstead of walking entire trees in `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`, pass the already-computed `committedFileSet` (from `filesChangedInCommit`) into `calculateSessionAttributions`.\\n\\nThen `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` only needs to:\\n1. For agent-touched files (`filesTouched`): read content + diff (already does this, fast)\\n2. For non-agent files: filter `committedFileSet - filesTouched`, read content + diff\\n\\nThis changes attribution from O(total repo files) to O(files in commit). Expected improvement: 4.7s → <50ms.\\n\\nFor `resolveTreesAndDiff`, replace `filesChangedInCommit` with `git diff-tree` CLI call, or pass the committed file list from `git status` if available. Expected improvement: 703ms → <50ms.\\n\\n**Total expected improvement: ~5.4s → ~200-300ms** (mostly OpenRepository + content overlap detection).\\n\\n## Alternative Considered: Background Post-Commit\\n\\nWe investigated backgrounding post-commit work using detached subprocess (same pattern as `telemetry/detached_unix.go`). This is viable but has tradeoffs:\\n\\n- Race conditions with rapid sequential commits\\n- Session state consistency between sync/background phases\\n- `entire explain` may not find checkpoint data immediately after commit\\n- Testing complexity\\n\\n**Recommendation: Fix the O(n) tree walks first.** This should reduce commit time from 5.4s to <500ms, likely eliminating the need for backgrounding. If still too slow after optimization, backgrounding remains available as a follow-up.\\n\\n## Existing Benchmarks\\n\\n`postcommit_bench_test.go` has benchmarks but uses tiny repos (5 files). Results (~60-70ms) don't reflect real-world performance. Consider adding a benchmark with a larger synthetic repo to catch O(n) regressions.\\n\\n## Files Referenced\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit, postCommitProcessSession\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession, calculateSessionAttributions\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated, getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees (ROOT CAUSE)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap.go` — filesOverlapWithContent, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` — OpenRepository, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/postcommit_bench_test.go` — existing benchmarks\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":159030,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"output_tokens\":1718,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":159030,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYgvgpQHXkpECQgKp2Khg\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"edda70d7-48ce-4364-9008-13d1fbce8d26\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:22:03.401Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"edda70d7-48ce-4364-9008-13d1fbce8d26\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"37360caf-91ff-4b81-8112-c444051a3608\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"15baaf39e5836b37@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T08:48:40.349Z\"},\"cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"9eed2800f50ea73a@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T08:48:40.349Z\"},\"tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T22:22:03.457Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:21:23.098Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"edda70d7-48ce-4364-9008-13d1fbce8d26\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Write\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01VarZyj11kPWsSzK55MpJQ1\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01VarZyj11kPWsSzK55MpJQ1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:22:03.991Z\",\"uuid\":\"01c504c8-382d-4eb8-a749-a9bda6c0d7f6\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"edda70d7-48ce-4364-9008-13d1fbce8d26\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01VarZyj11kPWsSzK55MpJQ1\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3/tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"eed19baa-7f42-4eb3-8a38-9c1feeb44184\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:22:03.989Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"create\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3/tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md\",\"content\":\"# Commit Hook Performance Investigation\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nUsers report commit hooks are slow. Measured **6.3 seconds** for a simple commit in a large repo (rust-lang, ~58k files).\\n\\n## Timing Instrumentation\\n\\nAdded timing logs to `PrepareCommitMsg`, `PostCommit`, and `CondenseSession`. Tested on rust-lang repo (~58k files), single session (idle), 1 file committed.\\n\\nBranch with instrumentation: `alex/investigate-commit-slowness`\\n\\nFiles modified:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — timing in PrepareCommitMsg + PostCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — timing in CondenseSession\\n\\nTo read results: `grep 'timing' .entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n## Measured Breakdown\\n\\n### prepare-commit-msg: ~121ms total\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 104ms | go-git PlainOpenWithOptions |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.3ms | |\\n| filterSessionsWithNewContent | 114ms | Content overlap detection |\\n\\n### post-commit: ~5,436ms total (5.4s) — THE BOTTLENECK\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 0.08ms | Likely cached from prepare-commit-msg |\\n| Head+CommitObject | 0.1ms | |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.1ms | |\\n| **resolveTreesAndDiff** | **703ms** | `filesChangedInCommit` walks both HEAD and parent trees |\\n| **processSession[0] (idle)** | **4,712ms** | Condensation of one session |\\n| processSession[1] (ended) | 0.8ms | |\\n| shadowBranchCleanup | 16ms | |\\n\\n### Inside processSession — CondenseSession: ~4,706ms\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms | |\\n| **calculateAttribution** | **4,685ms** | **86% of total commit time** |\\n| WriteCommitted | 18ms | |\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n### Primary: `calculateAttribution` — 4.7s (86% of total)\\n\\n`CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated()` in `manual_commit_attribution.go` calls `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees(ctx, baseTree, headTree)` at line ~229.\\n\\nThis function:\\n1. Calls `baseTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in base tree\\n2. Calls `headTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in HEAD tree\\n3. Builds two hash maps of every file path → blob hash\\n4. Compares to find changed files\\n\\nThis is **O(total files in repo)** when it should be **O(files changed in commit)**.\\n\\nThe `committedFileSet` (files changed in this commit) is already computed by `filesChangedInCommit` earlier in PostCommit. Attribution only needs to diff non-agent files from this set, not discover them by walking entire trees.\\n\\n### Secondary: `resolveTreesAndDiff` — 703ms\\n\\n`filesChangedInCommit()` in `common.go` also walks both HEAD and parent trees to find changed files. Same O(n) full-tree-walk problem.\\n\\nCould be replaced with `git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r HEAD~1 HEAD` which uses git's internal index and is much faster than go-git tree iteration.\\n\\n### Everything else is fast\\n\\n| Operation | Time |\\n|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository (first call) | 104ms |\\n| OpenRepository (second call) | <1ms |\\n| Session state listing | <1ms |\\n| Content overlap detection | 114ms |\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms |\\n| WriteCommitted (tree build + commit on checkpoints branch) | 18ms |\\n| Shadow branch cleanup | 16ms |\\n\\n## Proposed Fix: Pass committedFileSet to Attribution\\n\\nInstead of walking entire trees in `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`, pass the already-computed `committedFileSet` (from `filesChangedInCommit`) into `calculateSessionAttributions`.\\n\\nThen `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` only needs to:\\n1. For agent-touched files (`filesTouched`): read content + diff (already does this, fast)\\n2. For non-agent files: filter `committedFileSet - filesTouched`, read content + diff\\n\\nThis changes attribution from O(total repo files) to O(files in commit). Expected improvement: 4.7s → <50ms.\\n\\nFor `resolveTreesAndDiff`, replace `filesChangedInCommit` with `git diff-tree` CLI call, or pass the committed file list from `git status` if available. Expected improvement: 703ms → <50ms.\\n\\n**Total expected improvement: ~5.4s → ~200-300ms** (mostly OpenRepository + content overlap detection).\\n\\n## Alternative Considered: Background Post-Commit\\n\\nWe investigated backgrounding post-commit work using detached subprocess (same pattern as `telemetry/detached_unix.go`). This is viable but has tradeoffs:\\n\\n- Race conditions with rapid sequential commits\\n- Session state consistency between sync/background phases\\n- `entire explain` may not find checkpoint data immediately after commit\\n- Testing complexity\\n\\n**Recommendation: Fix the O(n) tree walks first.** This should reduce commit time from 5.4s to <500ms, likely eliminating the need for backgrounding. If still too slow after optimization, backgrounding remains available as a follow-up.\\n\\n## Existing Benchmarks\\n\\n`postcommit_bench_test.go` has benchmarks but uses tiny repos (5 files). Results (~60-70ms) don't reflect real-world performance. Consider adding a benchmark with a larger synthetic repo to catch O(n) regressions.\\n\\n## Files Referenced\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit, postCommitProcessSession\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession, calculateSessionAttributions\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated, getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees (ROOT CAUSE)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap.go` — filesOverlapWithContent, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` — OpenRepository, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/postcommit_bench_test.go` — existing benchmarks\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[],\"originalFile\":null},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"edda70d7-48ce-4364-9008-13d1fbce8d26\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"eed19baa-7f42-4eb3-8a38-9c1feeb44184\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01NuWoizotEgc5kbxB8DTUD1\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Written to `tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md`. Key takeaway: the 4.7s is from walking all 58k files twice in attribution when we only need the ~1 file that changed. Fix is to pass the already-computed `committedFileSet` — should bring the whole commit from 5.4s to under 500ms.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1763,\"cache_read_in