on — CondenseSession: ~4,706ms\\n    42→\\n    43→| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n    44→|---|---|---|\\n    45→| extractSessionData | 2.5ms | |\\n    46→| **calculateAttribution** | **4,685ms** | **86% of total commit time** |\\n    47→| WriteCommitted | 18ms | |\\n    48→\\n    49→## Root Cause\\n    50→\\n    51→### Primary: `calculateAttribution` — 4.7s (86% of total)\\n    52→\\n    53→`CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated()` in `manual_commit_attribution.go` calls `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees(ctx, baseTree, headTree)` at line ~229.\\n    54→\\n    55→This function:\\n    56→1. Calls `baseTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in base tree\\n    57→2. Calls `headTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in HEAD tree\\n    58→3. Builds two hash maps of every file path → blob hash\\n    59→4. Compares to find changed files\\n    60→\\n    61→This is **O(total files in repo)** when it should be **O(files changed in commit)**.\\n    62→\\n    63→The `committedFileSet` (files changed in this commit) is already computed by `filesChangedInCommit` earlier in PostCommit. Attribution only needs to diff non-agent files from this set, not discover them by walking entire trees.\\n    64→\\n    65→### Secondary: `resolveTreesAndDiff` — 703ms\\n    66→\\n    67→`filesChangedInCommit()` in `common.go` also walks both HEAD and parent trees to find changed files. Same O(n) full-tree-walk problem.\\n    68→\\n    69→Could be replaced with `git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r HEAD~1 HEAD` which uses git's internal index and is much faster than go-git tree iteration.\\n    70→\\n    71→### Everything else is fast\\n    72→\\n    73→| Operation | Time |\\n    74→|---|---|\\n    75→| OpenRepository (first call) | 104ms |\\n    76→| OpenRepository (second call) | <1ms |\\n    77→| Session state listing | <1ms |\\n    78→| Content overlap detection | 114ms |\\n    79→| extractSessionData | 2.5ms |\\n    80→| WriteCommitted (tree build + commit on checkpoints branch) | 18ms |\\n    81→| Shadow branch cleanup | 16ms |\\n    82→\\n    83→## Proposed Fix: Pass committedFileSet to Attribution\\n    84→\\n    85→Instead of walking entire trees in `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`, pass the already-computed `committedFileSet` (from `filesChangedInCommit`) into `calculateSessionAttributions`.\\n    86→\\n    87→Then `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` only needs to:\\n    88→1. For agent-touched files (`filesTouched`): read content + diff (already does this, fast)\\n    89→2. For non-agent files: filter `committedFileSet - filesTouched`, read content + diff\\n    90→\\n    91→This changes attribution from O(total repo files) to O(files in commit). Expected improvement: 4.7s → <50ms.\\n    92→\\n    93→For `resolveTreesAndDiff`, replace `filesChangedInCommit` with `git diff-tree` CLI call, or pass the committed file list from `git status` if available. Expected improvement: 703ms → <50ms.\\n    94→\\n    95→**Total expected improvement: ~5.4s → ~200-300ms** (mostly OpenRepository + content overlap detection).\\n    96→\\n    97→## Alternative Considered: Background Post-Commit\\n    98→\\n    99→We investigated backgrounding post-commit work using detached subprocess (same pattern as `telemetry/detached_unix.go`). This is viable but has tradeoffs:\\n   100→\\n   101→- Race conditions with rapid sequential commits\\n   102→- Session state consistency between sync/background phases\\n   103→- `entire explain` may not find checkpoint data immediately after commit\\n   104→- Testing complexity\\n   105→\\n   106→**Recommendation: Fix the O(n) tree walks first.** This should reduce commit time from 5.4s to <500ms, likely eliminating the need for backgrounding. If still too slow after optimization, backgrounding remains available as a follow-up.\\n   107→\\n   108→## Existing Benchmarks\\n   109→\\n   110→`postcommit_bench_test.go` has benchmarks but uses tiny repos (5 files). Results (~60-70ms) don't reflect real-world performance. Consider adding a benchmark with a larger synthetic repo to catch O(n) regressions.\\n   111→\\n   112→## Files Referenced\\n   113→\\n   114→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit, postCommitProcessSession\\n   115→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession, calculateSessionAttributions\\n   116→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated, getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees (ROOT CAUSE)\\n   117→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap.go` — filesOverlapWithContent, filesChangedInCommit\\n   118→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` — OpenRepository, filesChangedInCommit\\n   119→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/postcommit_bench_test.go` — existing benchmarks\\n   120→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"135deccb-e2fe-4de6-bfca-09c09e842c7e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:22:33.336Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3/tmp/commit-hook-perf-findings.md\",\"content\":\"# Commit Hook Performance Investigation\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nUsers report commit hooks are slow. Measured **6.3 seconds** for a simple commit in a large repo (rust-lang, ~58k files).\\n\\n## Timing Instrumentation\\n\\nAdded timing logs to `PrepareCommitMsg`, `PostCommit`, and `CondenseSession`. Tested on rust-lang repo (~58k files), single session (idle), 1 file committed.\\n\\nBranch with instrumentation: `alex/investigate-commit-slowness`\\n\\nFiles modified:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — timing in PrepareCommitMsg + PostCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — timing in CondenseSession\\n\\nTo read results: `grep 'timing' .entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n## Measured Breakdown\\n\\n### prepare-commit-msg: ~121ms total\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 104ms | go-git PlainOpenWithOptions |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.3ms | |\\n| filterSessionsWithNewContent | 114ms | Content overlap detection |\\n\\n### post-commit: ~5,436ms total (5.4s) — THE BOTTLENECK\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository | 0.08ms | Likely cached from prepare-commit-msg |\\n| Head+CommitObject | 0.1ms | |\\n| findSessionsForWorktree | 0.1ms | |\\n| **resolveTreesAndDiff** | **703ms** | `filesChangedInCommit` walks both HEAD and parent trees |\\n| **processSession[0] (idle)** | **4,712ms** | Condensation of one session |\\n| processSession[1] (ended) | 0.8ms | |\\n| shadowBranchCleanup | 16ms | |\\n\\n### Inside processSession — CondenseSession: ~4,706ms\\n\\n| Phase | Duration | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms | |\\n| **calculateAttribution** | **4,685ms** | **86% of total commit time** |\\n| WriteCommitted | 18ms | |\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n### Primary: `calculateAttribution` — 4.7s (86% of total)\\n\\n`CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated()` in `manual_commit_attribution.go` calls `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees(ctx, baseTree, headTree)` at line ~229.\\n\\nThis function:\\n1. Calls `baseTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in base tree\\n2. Calls `headTree.Files().ForEach()` — walks ALL ~58k files in HEAD tree\\n3. Builds two hash maps of every file path → blob hash\\n4. Compares to find changed files\\n\\nThis is **O(total files in repo)** when it should be **O(files changed in commit)**.\\n\\nThe `committedFileSet` (files changed in this commit) is already computed by `filesChangedInCommit` earlier in PostCommit. Attribution only needs to diff non-agent files from this set, not discover them by walking entire trees.\\n\\n### Secondary: `resolveTreesAndDiff` — 703ms\\n\\n`filesChangedInCommit()` in `common.go` also walks both HEAD and parent trees to find changed files. Same O(n) full-tree-walk problem.\\n\\nCould be replaced with `git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r HEAD~1 HEAD` which uses git's internal index and is much faster than go-git tree iteration.\\n\\n### Everything else is fast\\n\\n| Operation | Time |\\n|---|---|\\n| OpenRepository (first call) | 104ms |\\n| OpenRepository (second call) | <1ms |\\n| Session state listing | <1ms |\\n| Content overlap detection | 114ms |\\n| extractSessionData | 2.5ms |\\n| WriteCommitted (tree build + commit on checkpoints branch) | 18ms |\\n| Shadow branch cleanup | 16ms |\\n\\n## Proposed Fix: Pass committedFileSet to Attribution\\n\\nInstead of walking entire trees in `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`, pass the already-computed `committedFileSet` (from `filesChangedInCommit`) into `calculateSessionAttributions`.\\n\\nThen `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` only needs to:\\n1. For agent-touched files (`filesTouched`): read content + diff (already does this, fast)\\n2. For non-agent files: filter `committedFileSet - filesTouched`, read content + diff\\n\\nThis changes attribution from O(total repo files) to O(files in commit). Expected improvement: 4.7s → <50ms.\\n\\nFor `resolveTreesAndDiff`, replace `filesChangedInCommit` with `git diff-tree` CLI call, or pass the committed file list from `git status` if available. Expected improvement: 703ms → <50ms.\\n\\n**Total expected improvement: ~5.4s → ~200-300ms** (mostly OpenRepository + content overlap detection).\\n\\n## Alternative Considered: Background Post-Commit\\n\\nWe investigated backgrounding post-commit work using detached subprocess (same pattern as `telemetry/detached_unix.go`). This is viable but has tradeoffs:\\n\\n- Race conditions with rapid sequential commits\\n- Session state consistency between sync/background phases\\n- `entire explain` may not find checkpoint data immediately after commit\\n- Testing complexity\\n\\n**Recommendation: Fix the O(n) tree walks first.** This should reduce commit time from 5.4s to <500ms, likely eliminating the need for backgrounding. If still too slow after optimization, backgrounding remains available as a follow-up.\\n\\n## Existing Benchmarks\\n\\n`postcommit_bench_test.go` has benchmarks but uses tiny repos (5 files). Results (~60-70ms) don't reflect real-world performance. Consider adding a benchmark with a larger synthetic repo to catch O(n) regressions.\\n\\n## Files Referenced\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit, postCommitProcessSession\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession, calculateSessionAttributions\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated, getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees (ROOT CAUSE)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap.go` — filesOverlapWithContent, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` — OpenRepository, filesChangedInCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/postcommit_bench_test.go` — existing benchmarks\\n\",\"numLines\":120,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":120}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"b1794dc4-9453-475b-b8a4-c867d5d68137\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"135deccb-e2fe-4de6-bfca-09c09e842c7e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015P4X5GctYQrkT5E8nMVzvv\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good, I've re-read the findings doc. Two fixes to implement:\\n\\n1. **Primary (4.7s):** Pass `committedFileSet` into `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` so it doesn't walk entire trees\\n2. **Secondary (703ms):** Replace `filesChangedInCommit` go-git tree walk with `git diff-tree`\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2114,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":160887,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2114},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inferen