uld be double-counting.\\n\\nUnless... the attribution is designed to capture the FULL session attribution, not just the delta. And the accumulated PromptAttributions track the intermediate user edits.\\n\\nSo the real question is whether we actually need the session-start-to-HEAD range or if the committed file set would suffice—they're comparing different time windows, but I'm wondering if that divergence matters in practice.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":57,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":110342,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":57},\"output_tokens\":10,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYh4pXo45v3N6116m6wGA\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c30f17bd-9b18-484d-b625-b8de97086ee2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T00:08:35.913Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c30f17bd-9b18-484d-b625-b8de97086ee2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/investigate-commit-slowness\",\"slug\":\"optimized-bubbling-widget\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WviTjGimSQ2zeWeX4jJdeP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good question. They're actually comparing **different ranges**:\\n\\n- `filesChangedInCommit`: **HEAD~1 → HEAD** (files in this one commit)\\n- `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`: **baseTree → headTree** where baseTree = `state.AttributionBaseCommit` (files changed since session/attribution base)\\n\\nSo the question is: can `AttributionBaseCommit` differ from HEAD~1?\\n\\nLet me check what happens to `AttributionBaseCommit` after condensation.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":57,\"cache_