ses null-separated output, returns set of changed file paths. For initial commits (empty commit1), use `git diff-tree --root -r -z <commit2>`.\\n- `DiffTreeFileList(ctx context.Context, commit1, commit2 string) ([]string, error)` — same but returns `[]string` (attribution needs a list, not a set). Or just have one function returning both/either — decide during implementation.\\n\\n### 2. Replace `filesChangedInCommit`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\nReplace the body of `filesChangedInCommit` (line 2174) to call `gitops.DiffTreeFiles(ctx, parentHash, headHash)`.\\n\\nSignature changes — needs `ctx` and commit hash strings instead of go-git tree objects. Update the call site at line 836. The pre-resolved `headTree`/`parentTree` are still needed by other callers (content overlap, carry-forward, attribution), so don't remove those — just stop passing them to `filesChangedInCommit`.\\n\\n### 3. Replace `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` in attribution\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go`\\n\\nReplace the call at line 229:\\n```go\\nnonAgentFiles, err := getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees(ctx, baseTree, headTree)\\n```\\nwith a call to `gitops.DiffTreeFiles(ctx, attributionBaseCommit, headCommit)`.\\n\\nThis requires threading the commit hash strings into `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated`. Add a new parameter or options struct for the commit hashes.\\n\\n**Call chain to update:**\\n- `PostCommit` → `postCommitProcessSession` → `CondenseSession` → `calculateSessionAttributions` → `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated`\\n- Thread `attributionBaseCommit` (from `state.AttributionBaseCommit`) and `headCommitHash` (from `head.Hash().String()`) through `attributionOpts`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\n- Add commit hash fields to `attributionOpts` struct (line 307)\\n- Pass them from `CondenseSession` → `calculateSessionAttributions` → `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated`\\n\\n### 4. Handle `CondenseSessionByID` (doctor command)\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` (line 743)\\n\\n`CondenseSessionByID` calls `CondenseSession` without a specific commit context. When commit hashes aren't available, fall back to the current go-git tree walk (or skip non-agent attribution). This is a salvage path, not performance-critical.\\n\\n### 5. Update tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution_test.go`\\n\\n- Update `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` call sites for new signature\\n- `TestGetAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` (line 777) — delete (function removed)\\n- `TestCalculateAttributionWithAccumulated_UserEditsNonAgentFile` (line 697) — key test, update to pass commit hashes; may need a real git repo fixture instead of in-memory trees for the non-agent file detection path\\n\\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff_test.go`\\n- Test `DiffTreeFiles` with a real git repo (create temp repo, make commits, verify output)\\n- Test initial commit (no parent) case\\n- Test multi-commit range\\n\\n### 6. Remove dead code\\n\\n- Delete `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` from `manual_commit_attribution.go`\\n- Delete `TestGetAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` from test file\\n\\n### 7. Remove timing instrumentation\\n\\nRemove the timing `logging.Info` calls added during investigation from:\\n- `manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg and PostCommit timing logs\\n- `manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession timing logs\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff.go`** (new) — `DiffTreeFiles` using `git diff-tree`\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff_test.go`** (new) — tests for above\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — update `filesChangedInCommit` + remove timing logs\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — new params, remove `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — thread commit